title: Democratic Hopes Rise on Senate Control as Two States Count Votes
description: In Arizona and Nevada, Republicans’ path to victory appeared to narrow, though both races remain close. The G.O.P.’s odds of success are greater in the House.
dc:creator: Blake Hounshell
media:credit: Alisha Jucevic for The New York Times
media:description: As ballots were counted in Arizona, Senator Mark Kelly was ahead of Blake Masters, his Republican rival. The state’s race for governor was significantly tighter.
